<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idca8a10bf-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2101"><num value="2101">§ 2101.</num><heading> Findings</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Congress finds that—</chapeau><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idca8a10c0-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2101/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> States have the responsibility for management of a broad range of living and nonliving resources in State waters and submerged lands; and</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idca8a10c1-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598" identifier="/us/usc/t43/s2101/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> included in the range of resources are certain abandoned shipwrecks, which have been deserted and to which the owner has relinquished ownership rights with no retention.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idca8a10c2-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/298/s2">Pub. L. 100–298, § 2</ref>, <date date="1988-04-28">Apr. 28, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/432">102 Stat. 432</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idca8a10c3-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idca8a10c4-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="shortTitle" id="idca8a10c5-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Short Title</heading><p><ref href="/us/pl/100/298/s1">Pub. L. 100–298, § 1</ref>, <date date="1988-04-28">Apr. 28, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/432">102 Stat. 432</ref>, provided that: <quotedContent origin="/us/pl/100/298/s1">“This Act [enacting this chapter] may be cited as the ‘Abandoned Shipwreck Act of 1987’.”</quotedContent>
</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
